    "stem": "It is July. A regional telephone company treasurer expects to have $1 million cash in about six weeks and intends to buy 90-day T-bills. Cash bills are now selling at 94.42. Fearing a fall in interest rates, the treasurer buys one September T-bill futures contract at 94.64. Six weeks later, the treasurer buys cash bills at 95.02 and offsets the futures at 95.14. Ignoring transaction costs, what is the effective price for the cash T-bills?",
