    "stem": "A bond dealer buys $10 million face value of cash Treasury bonds for inventory at 115-30. To hedge against a rise in interest rates, the dealer sells 100 T-bond futures contracts at 116-10. Two weeks later, the dealer sells the cash bonds at 115-26 and lifts the hedge at 116-01. Ignoring transaction costs, what profit or loss did the dealer make on the combined cash and futures transactions?",
