    "stem": "It is April 15. A corporate treasurer will have $1 million cash on hand in four months and intends to buy Treasury bonds, but fears interest rates will fall. The treasurer buys 10 T-bond futures and lifts the hedge on August 15. Futures are quoted in 32nds of a percentage point of $100,000 face value. April 15 cash is 116-26 and December futures are 116-28; August 15 cash is 119-02 and December futures are 118-20. What is the result of the futures transaction?",
